## 13. Naming and Organization Rules

### File Names

- Use kebab-case for new files: `control-bar.tsx`, `statistics-charts.tsx`, `gear-table.tsx`, `icons.tsx`, `gear.ts`.
- Pages and layouts use Next.js reserved names: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `route.ts`.
- Prefer kebab-case for all modules and components. Legacy PascalCase files (e.g., `GearTable.tsx`) will be migrated to kebab-case; a temporary re-export (`gear-table.tsx`) exists for compatibility.

### Folder Names

- Use kebab-case for directories.
- Route groups: `(group-name)`.
- Shared components live in `src/components`. Page-specific components can be colocated under the route when they are not reused.
- Server-side data access for a domain is centralized in `src/app/lib/<domain>.ts` (e.g., `gear.ts`). Avoid scattering queries across routes.
- Do not create `src/features/*` unless a cross-route, cross-domain feature truly requires it. Default to App Router colocation and shared `components/`.

